			<a name="2"><font face="verdana" size="3" color="#9f3215"><b>    A few morning posts from Abashi</b></font>
			<br>
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			<b><a href="mailto:catalyst@everlore.com">Catalyst</a>
			</font><font face="verdana" size="2" color="#9f3215">
			</b></font>[<font face="verdana" size="1" color="black">8/15/2000 10:45:35 AM PST</font>] <font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			<b><a href="newsinfo.asp?ID=199387">
			Add Comment
			</a></b></font>
			<br>
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black"><Blockquote>
<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/004886.html">Just an FYI for people using Scale of Wolf... Verifed this today... :(</a></B><P>

For those of us actually using Scale of Wolf (I know... all 2 of us...), it has gone back to being dropped if you are cast upon. Doesn't help those of us that are trying to travel from place to place. <P>

<B>I do know that we put a change in a while ago that stopped it from dropping on the basis of being on the receiving end of a melee attack, but am not absolutely certain that spells were included. I'll check into it further tomorrow.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/004876.html">Gordon..lie?</a></B><P>

Matching up weapon-type for weapon type, the monks worst set (bare knuck) versus the warriors worst (dual ssoy's), the monk outdamaged the warrior by nearly 25%. Best versus best, the monks outdamaged by just over 25%. The lowest difference obtained for appropriate equipment was still a 20% surplus to monks. (The worst armed monk versus the best armed warrior still favored the monk by 10%.) <P>

How can the warrior out damage the monk when you say the test still favored the monk by 10%? Now..im not saying you didnt perform these tests but this "confusion" doesnt account well with it. Is Gordon trapped in a web of lies? Did he really test it? Or is he just not typing intelligently.<P>

<B>You might want to read the sentence you found issue with again:<P>

"The worst ***armed monk*** versus the best ***armed warrior*** still favored the monk by 10%"<P>

I added emphasis to the appropriate places. The case where the warrior outdamaged the monk was when the monk was ***unarmed*** and the warrior was armed with is best weapon. Every case where the monk used a weapon, he outdamaged the warrior.<P>

I understand that this confusion was accidental, but in the future I would like to politely request that you be certain before breaking out accusations of lying. It's very offensive.<P>

-Gordon</B><P>

<HR align="center" width="75%"><P>

<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/004807.html">GM Events?</a></B><P>

How do I find out more about GM hosted events? I have been playing EQ since release but i always missed those events. Is there anywhere i can find out when is the next event on my server (Mith marr). Thanks <P>

<B>"Events", meaning things like the tests, will soon be posted on the EverQuest.com web page. Quests, however, are another matter, as they are never pre-announced. You'll only be able to find out about them by either being on and involved at the time, or by reading up on them afterwards. We'll soon have quest-stories posted on the official website.<P>

-Gordon</B>
</blockquote>
		<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
		
		
			
