<B><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum2/HTML/000745.html">Wizard Draughts are large and slow</a></B><P>

1) Post-50 Wizards don't need the missing large DD spells, because a double cast of Draught does the job (so Draughts are "large" if cast twice...) but<BR>
2) Draughts are swift in single-cast, but "slow" in chain-cast, and this might be the hidden reason why some post-50 Wizards feel less effective than before. I suspect Draughts need a cast time of 2.5 instead of 3; the level 60 Sunstrike could also be given a shorter cast time (same as Ice Comet).<P>

<B>The Draught line was created to give wizards the option of doing less damage at similar mana/damage ratio compared to ice comet, and also to give them similar spells across the three elements that the wizards control. The reasoning behind "less damage" was to reduce the amount that the wizard would aggro the target. Had we wanted to continue along the same lines as ice comet, we could have given similar damage spells with equal damage, mana, and casting time requirements.<P>

In this case, the additional time required to stack two draughts versus one ice comet is what you "pay" for the reduced amount that you aggro the target. <P>

