			<a name="19"><font face="verdana" size="3" color="#9f3215"><b>    Tallon Zek: GM Event based in Neriak</b></font>
			<br>
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			<b><a href="mailto:RavageRydr@aol.com">Curlie</a>
			</font><font face="verdana" size="2" color="#9f3215">
			</b></font>[<font face="verdana" size="1" color="black">8/13/2000 12:09:52 PM PST</font>] <font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
			<b><a href="newsinfo.asp?ID=197751">
			8 Comments
			</a></b></font>
			<br>
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black"><Blockquote>
   There was a GM event Saturday, August 12th on the Tallon Zek Server.  I was lucky to be in it from the very beginning.  It started just outside Neriak with the appearance of A Royal Herald calling for someone to deliver a message for him.  Despite being the first to hail him, kneel to him, and ask for the privilege of the task, the guy next to me was chosen to deliver it.  But no big deal, as he let a Troll Shaman and myself accompany him on the journey.<P>

   We were sent to the East Commons/North Ro tunnel where we met a DE Rogue named Tsajin K'Layn, who read the note and asked us to accompany her back to Neriak.  We did so and there she was greated by one of the high priests of Neriak, a fellow by the name of Dorvias N'Keth.  Tsajin wanted to talk to the king, but Dorvias wanted her to just deal with him.  They argued for a moment and then King Naythax Thex appeared and came to deal with Tsajin himself, much to Dorvias's protest.
   By this time a crowd had gathered and it was getting difficult to see and hear, but I managed to secure a spot near the front to watch.  Evidently a book had been taken by some fiends in Najena, and Thex wanted Tsajin to retrieve it, and promised her a tenth of all the treasury for it.  Tsajin accepted, and asked all who were there to accompany her to get the book.  She also rewarded the person who had been sent by the Herald to get her, she gave him 90pp, which he split with the troll and myself evenly.<P>

   So we were off to Najena!  Once outside the city she asked if someone would lead the way.  An ogre who had been crowding and shouting the entire time the king had been talking (name witheld so as not to defame him) said that he would lead, but then said he didn't know the way.  No one seemed to jump at the opportunity, so I said I would lead if no one else would.  Tsajin smiled at me, and I led us all over to Lavastorm.  Once inside Lavastorm, tsajin seemed to know the way and she took us over to Najena.<P>

   Outside Najena we were greeted by the witch Drelzna herself!  After a brief discussion with her (I want the book, no you can't have it) Tsajin attacked and we all followed suit, Drelzna lasted maybe 6 seconds, but it seemed she somehow escaped and we didn't get the book.  But luckily just then a dark elf prophet appeared and told Tsajin she had played her part in history, and gave her the book.  Tsajin tried to ask some questions, but the prophet disappeared.<P>

   We took the book back to Neriak and met the king back in the 3rd Gate area.  Tsajin asked for the reward, but Thex said the thanks of all the dark elves should be enough.  Tsajin asked for more, so the king (in a VERY well played and dramatically stated part) told his priest to take the book off her body after he was finished, and proceed to kill her himself.  I tried to heal her, as she had always been kind to me, but she seemed to just have all her life taken away suddenly (funny what kings can do) and she fell to the ground...<P>

   The loud, obnoxious ogre from earlier managed to ninja loot her corpse, and wound up with a Robe of Enshroudment.  And the king too the book over to the weird pillar right near the entrance of 3rd Gate.  There, he proceeded to sacrifice a high elf girl and offer her blood up to Innoruuk.  It was at this point that I noticed the prophet at the back of the crowd.  I worked my way back to him and told him what had happened.  He merely replied that he knew... and it occured to me that being a prophet of course he knew... and he pretty much kept silent from then on.<P>

   Shortly after the slaying of the elf girl a beam of light shined upon the top of the small pillar/island and the Avatar of Hate popped in!  Everybody was amazed, and nothing happened for quite a while while everyone was shouting.  I glanced over at the prophet and saw him cast a spell on the Avatar.  Unfortunately I don't know what the spell was, but i believe it gave the 'smiles at Avatar of Hate.  Ahhh that feels much better...' effect, and when I looked back the Avatar was gone.<P>

   The prophet ran up to the island spot where the king and Dorvias were.  The king asked what he had learned for the Avatar, and the prophet gave a vague reference to a child that was protected from Lanys  (I would assume Lanys T'vyl), and the king gave a rant how Lanys was no longer needed, and was a waste of Innoruuk's power.  He said something about reclaiming the energy she used, and asked more about the child.  The prophet said the child was in a place so well protected that Lanys could not enter... Befallen.<P>

   The king thanked all the people and said that he would need us again soon, then he and everyone with him left, including the prophet.  A large group of us tried running over to Befallen, but nothing happened there.<P>

  The event was lots of fun and the story was great, although a few parts seemed a little confusing.  Many of the people involved loved to shout and run through the middle of everything, which really hurt the overall effect.  Sometimes King Thex even had to hold up the proceedings until people calmed down.  I was kinda disappointed nobody got some sort of a reward at the end (I was kinda hoping since I had been along the whole time and was an active participant i would get something, but I did get my 30pp earlier, so I can't complain) and a lot of us were pissed the noisy ogre looted the robe, but it was still lots of fun and I hope the story continues when I am on.<P>

P.S.  This event was the same night as when Rubicite started dropping in Najena, but I'm sure someone else will post about that...
</blockquote>
